title: Italy Locks Down Northern Region, and U.S. Coronavirus Cases Pass 400
description: Italy announced a plan to restrict the movement of a fourth of its population. New York declared a state of emergency. Here’s the latest.

title: Inside Trump Administration, Debate Raged Over What to Tell Public
description: The administration’s response to the coronavirus has repeatedly matched public health experts against a hesitant White House, where worry of panic dominates.

title: China May Be Beating the Coronavirus, at a Painful Cost
description: Beijing says its heavy-handed measures are working. Can other countries battling the outbreak learn from its efforts — or is the cure worse than the disease?

title: Anyone Who Wants a Coronavirus Test Can Have One, Trump Says. Not Quite, Says His Administration.
description: Key officials in recent days have corrected or clarified the president, who has sought to project calm as the coronavirus continues to spread in the United States.

title: Erik Prince Recruits Ex-Spies to Help Infiltrate Liberal Groups
description: Mr. Prince, a contractor close to the Trump administration, contacted veteran spies for operations by Project Veritas, the conservative group known for conducting stings on news organizations and other groups.

title: Fourth Time’s the Charm? Mark Meadows Takes Over Trump’s White House
description: Mr. Meadows, a retiring Republican congressman from North Carolina and one of President Trump’s most ardent defenders, becomes the latest chief of staff for a mercurial president who dispatched the previous three after they fell out of favor.

title: Modern Love Podcast: Lesley Manville Reads ‘The Kindness, and Xanax, of Strangers’
description: The “Ordinary Love” actress reads an essay about breast cancer and the unexpected need for community.

title: Sign Up: ‘Coronavirus Briefing’
description: An informed guide to the global outbreak.

title: I’m Going to Die. I May as Well Be Cheerful About It.
description: While death is inevitable, our attitude about it is not.

title: Trump, His Eye on the Border, Overlooked the Coronavirus Threat
description: His insistence that the danger was overseas and could be kept out led officials to downplay the disease’s spread and the need for tests.

title: Trump’s Crazy Fantasy World
description: In what The Spectator calls “the Year of the Drunken Uncle,” three old guys vie for the presidency amid coronavirus fears and a careering stock market.

title: Why Watch Video in a Museum? Let Steve McQueen Show You
description: The Oscar-winning filmmaker never abandoned his first career as a fine artist. His meticulously staged Tate Modern exhibition puts his commitment on display.

title: Florida Woman Changed Voters’ Party Affiliations, Officials Say
description: Cheryl A. Hall falsified 10 registration forms, at least six of which enrolled Democratic and independent voters as Republicans, said the authorities, who are eyeing an additional 109 forms.

title: ‘Close Call’: NASA-Boeing Investigation of Starliner Flight Finds Lapses
description: The uncrewed December space mission could have ended in disaster.

title: Roundup of Saudi Royals Expands With Detention of a 4th Prince
description: The arrests have raised questions about whether the crown prince was on the verge of taking full power from his father, King Salman.

title: Veterans Are Working, but Not in Jobs That Match Their Advanced Training
description: Like most Americans, veterans have benefited from a robust labor market. But skills learned in combat do not always translate to private-sector jobs.

title: Wall Street Had 2 Terrible Weeks. Here’s How 7 Traders Dealt With It.
description: As anxiety about coronavirus gave way to fear, investors dumped shares, watched the news and fielded client calls. “I have no energy left to speak.”

title: Stop Your Phone From Using So Much Data
description: Data overages from your wireless carrier can add up quickly. Here’s how to keep your bill under control.

title: Get the Most Out of Your Fancy Smartphone Camera
description: The latest Apple and Google models have software that automatically enhances your photos, but you can also take control to get your perfect shot.

title: How to Respond to Microaggressions
description: Should you let that comment slide, or address it head on? Is it more harm than it’s worth? We can help.

title: Rome Celebrates the Short, but Beautiful, Life of Raphael
description: Amid new coronavirus restrictions on museums in Italy, a blockbuster show  traces the artist’s life from finish to start.

title: Fighting to Save Their Tribe From Termination
description: In her new novel, “The Night Watchman,” Louise Erdrich brings to light a political battle from the 1950s that still reverberates today.

title: Sneezing Dogs, Dancing Bees: How Animals Vote
description: The 2020 election is off to a complicated start. Maybe we can draw some comparative political lessons from the animal kingdom.

title: Try Our Newest Game
description: Play Vertex. Connect the dots to reveal the hidden picture.

title: The Mini, Tiles and More Games
description: Solve the daily puzzle edited by Will Shortz, or try our new games like Letter Boxed.

title: Try Spelling Bee
description: Puzzle throughout the day to see how many words you can find.
